  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fatigue is a frequent and disabling symptom in patients with multiple sclerosis (MS). The
      pathophysiology of this sign is not fully understood. Some data suggest that the fatigue is
      associated with sleep disorders. The aim of this study is to determine the polysomnographic
      parameters in MS patients with fatigue in comparison to MS patients without fatigue.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
